Sentencas: The current collector is one of the essential and critical components for reliable operation of the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Novel anode current collector for hydrocarbon fuel solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Here a novel anode current collector is proposed to enhance the electrochemical performance stability of the anode supported cell operated under hydrocarbon fuel.
Titulo: Novel anode current collector for hydrocarbon fuel solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A scandium modified nickel fiber felt (Sc: Ni-felt), and a pristine nickel felt (Ni-felt) are employed as the anode current collector to evaluate and compare the electrochemical performance and long-term stability under humidified methane.
Titulo: Novel anode current collector for hydrocarbon fuel solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of the cell measured using the Sc: Ni-felt current collector are 679, 528, and 389 mW cm(-2) at 800, 750, and 700 degrees C, respectively, under humidified CH4.
Titulo: Novel anode current collector for hydrocarbon fuel solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: 19%, 24%, and 28% in the power density is recorded compared to the cell tested with Ni-felt.
Titulo: Novel anode current collector for hydrocarbon fuel solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A load of 625 mA cm(-2) is applied to investigate the long-term stability of both cells.
Titulo: Novel anode current collector for hydrocarbon fuel solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell with the novel current collector exhibits excellent stability after 50 h, while the cell tested with Ni-felt gets deteriorated with time under the same operating condition.
Titulo: Novel anode current collector for hydrocarbon fuel solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Finally, the electrochemical impedance analysis under a constant load has been carried out to evaluate the effect of the Sc: Ni current collector on the electrochemical performance and stability of the cell.
